HEADWORD: pachonta
<hw>pa*chon"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A substance resembling gutta-percha, and used to adulterate it,
obtained from the East Indian tree <spn>Isonandra
acuminata</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

